T1  - Saving determinants in Colombia: 1925–19941This paper is part of a regional research project sponsored by the InterAmerican Development Bank. It has been presented at seminars at Fedesarrollo, the IDB, and at the 9th InterAmerican Seminar on Economics (NBER—Universidad de San Andrés) in Buenos Aires, Argentina, November 18–20, 1996. We would like to thank Sebastian Edwards, Martin Feldstein, Ricardo Hausmann, Santiago Herrera, Leonardo Letelier, Maurice Obstfeld, Roberto Steiner, Alejandro López and Jorge Streb, and an anonymous referee for comments. We are also grateful to Natalia Salazar and Raquel Bernal for their valuable help throughout the project. Fabio Sánchez generously provided the firm-level data.1
AU  - Cárdenas, Mauricio
AU  - Escobar, Andrés
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 57
IS  - 1
SP  - 5
